The paper discusses the use of GPU A-SGD to speed up training of large convolutional neural networks for computer vision, indicating that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of neural networks, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of parallelism in training the networks suggests that it may also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential for training larger networks on larger training sets, indicating that it may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the research, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
